Step 2 — Generate candidates based on your classification:
- International brand: include the parent company global domain (e.g. .com) as your highest confidence candidate
- Local UK business: prioritise .co.uk and .com variants
- Consider trading name abbreviations — "BUILDERS WAREHOUSE" → bw, "UNITED KINGDOM" → uk
- Remove suffixes: Ltd, PLC, Group, Holdings, UK, International, Europe, Limited
- Consider short versions of the name, initials, and common abbreviations

Step 3 — Assign confidence:
- 0.9+ only if you are highly confident (well-known brand, obvious domain)
- 0.5-0.8 for reasonable guesses
